comments: Reddish (LAL) legally contests Durant's (PHX) driving shot attempt, making "high-five" contact just after the release.
Nurkic (PHX) brushes James' (LAL) left arm and marginal contact occurs at the end of James' drive.
Beal (PHX) and Davis (LAL) make incidental leg/foot contact with one another as Davis rolls into the lane.
James (LAL) grasps and then quickly releases Nurkic's (PHX) left arm, and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Nurkic (PHX) maintains verticality and incidental body contact occurs during Prince's (LAL) layup attempt.
Durant (PHX) grasps Davis' (LAL) jersey as they each attempt to establish rebounding position and then quickly releases before they each elevate to pursue the loose ball.
Nurkic (PHX) raises his arm to pursue the rebound and incidental contact occurs with Davis' (LAL) left arm after the ball is cleanly back-tapped toward the corner by Durant (PHX).
Davis (LAL) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Durant (PHX) and Davis (LAL) engage and disengage with one another as marginal contact occurs after the release of the jump shot attempt.

Davis (LAL) establishes himself in Beal's (PHX) path and does not deliver illegal contact as he sets the pick. Davis and Beal then make incidental foot contact with one another as Davis is rolling toward the lane following the expiration of the pick.
Prince (LAL) extends forward prior to marginal contact occurring with Durant's (PHX) side and front as Durant receives the pass.
Prince (LAL) extends his hands and initiates contact with Durant's (PHX) front at the top of the perimeter.
Reddish (LAL) cleanly deflects the ball as simultaneous incidental arm contact occurs with Durant (PHX) on the wing.
Durant (PHX) legally goes into the backcourt to retrieve the loose ball after it is deflected by Reddish (LAL).
Reddish (LAL) is trailing Durant (PHX) from behind when marginal contact occurs with Durant's left arm/back as Durant slows his momentum near the free throw line during the drive.
Nurkic (PHX) brings both hands forward toward Reddish's (LAL) back and marginal contact occurs as they each attempt to establish rebounding position.
Gordon (PHX) brings both hands forward and marginal contact occurs with Davis' (LAL) front and left arm prior to Davis passing.
Beal (PHX) brings his arm toward the ball and marginal contact occurs with Prince's (LAL) lower body prior to Prince's gather.
Reddish (LAL) moves somewhat laterally prior to marginal body contact occurring with Durant (PHX) during the drive.
Durant (PHX) releases his off-arm away from Reddish's (LAL) front and marginal contact occurs after they come together at the same spot during the drive.
Davis (LAL) and Durant (PHX) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.

Replay review of the foul called on Beal (PHX) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Beal makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Reaves (LAL) prior to incidental contact occurring. Beal had the ball at the time of the whistle and Phoenix was subsequently awarded possession following the review.
Reaves (LAL) and Allen (PHX) each make contact with the ball as simultaneous incidental side-to-side contact occurs during the rebound.
Bates-Diop (PHX) does not make intentional leg-to-ball contact as the ball is loose on the floor.
After James (LAL) already has control of the loose ball, Davis (LAL) turns toward Bates-Diop (PHX) and extends his forearm slightly, causing marginal contact to occur.
Allen (PHX) commits a take foul on James (LAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Allen (PHX) commits a take foul on Davis (LAL).
Prince (LAL) legally contests Gordon's (PHX) jump shot attempt.
